# Phase 21.3: SetList Name and Save Functionality

This plan details the implementation of a combobox for SetList names, protection against losing unsaved changes, handling empty/existing SetList names, and enabling deletion of entire SetLists.

## User Review Required
> [!IMPORTANT]
> - **Combobox UI**: I will replace the current `RawAutocomplete` with a `DropdownMenu` (or a custom `TextField` with a dropdown button) to satisfy the "textbox + dropdown" requirement while matching the existing dark theme.
> - **Existing Name Alert**: When saving an initially unnamed SetList, if the entered name already exists, the plan specifies showing an alert ("SetList name already exists") and **blocking the save**. *Question: Would you prefer this alert to have an "Overwrite" option instead of just blocking the save?*

## Proposed Changes

### [Setlist State Management]
#### [MODIFY] [setlist_providers.dart](file:///c:/Users/bhanu/projects/KeryxPro/lib/features/setlist/presentation/setlist_providers.dart)
- **Signature Tracking**: Add a provider (`activeSetlistSignatureProvider`) that tracks the exact item composition of the currently loaded or last-saved SetList.
- **Unsaved Changes Helper**: Create logic to compare the current SetList items against the `activeSetlistSignatureProvider` to accurately detect unsaved modifications.

### [Setlist Pane UI]
#### [MODIFY] [setlist_pane.dart](file:///c:/Users/bhanu/projects/KeryxPro/lib/features/dashboard/presentation/widgets/setlist_pane.dart)
- **Combobox Implementation**: 
  - Replace the SetList name `RawAutocomplete` widget with a combobox implementation that includes a dropdown arrow to view all existing names.
- **Loading with Confirmation**: 
  - When the user selects a saved list from the combobox, check for unsaved changes using the new signature tracking.
  - If unsaved changes exist, show an `AlertDialog`: "You have unsaved items. Do you want to clear them and load the selected list?".
- **Empty Name Save Flow**:
  - Update `_saveSetlist` to handle cases where the name is empty.
  - Show a dialog asking the user to enter a name.
  - If the name exists in `savedSetlistNamesProvider`, show the "SetList name already exists" alert and stop.
- **Delete Setlist Flow**:
  - Update the "Delete" button logic in the bottom toolbar. Enable it if there is an active item selection OR if the SetList is entirely empty but has an active name.
  - If the list is empty and the user presses delete, show an `AlertDialog`: "Are you sure you want to delete the SetList '[Name]'?". If confirmed, delete it from the database and clear the active name.
- **Empty Save Prevention**:
  - Add a validation check in `_saveSetlist`: `if (items.isEmpty)` show a snackbar or alert preventing the save.

## Verification Plan
### Manual Verification
- **Combobox**: Ensure the text box has a dropdown arrow and lists all saved SetLists.
- **Unsaved Confirmation**: Create a blank list, add an item, and select an existing list from the dropdown. Verify the confirmation dialog appears.
- **Empty Name Save**: Leave the name empty, add an item, press Save. Verify it asks for a name, and rejects names that already exist.
- **Empty Save Prevention**: Try to save an empty list. Verify it is blocked.
- **Delete SetList**: Load an existing list, click 'Clear All', then click the Delete icon. Verify it prompts to delete the SetList name and successfully removes it.
